##The COVID-19's primary hospital: Long Lines at fever clinics, shortages of supplies and a history of contact with infected areas

MICRO-SIGNAL BQSHENYIDU

Beijing Youth Daily reports from the official public number

Reporters Han Qian, Wei Xiaohan, Li Jianan, Zhang Fan, Yan Xingyue, Tong Xiaoyu, Liang Ting Li Dong Guo Huimin intern reporter Chen Weijing Long Tian Yin

Editor / Yang Baolu & Song Jianhua

COVID-19, the first confirmed case of pneumonia in Henan Province, was treated at the Taikang County People's Hospital on Jan. 8

As of 2400 hours on January 22, a total of 571 confirmed cases of pneumonia, including 95 severe cases and 17 deaths (all from Hubei Province) , had been reported from 25 provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities in China, according to the COVID-19. A total of 393 suspected cases were reported in 13 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) . In addition, a total of 25 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) reported the epidemic, adding 4 provinces in Hebei, Liaoning, Jiangsu and Fujian.

At 2:00 a.m. on the 23rd, Wuhan issued a notice of closure of the city. This is the "Wuhan COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic prevention and Control Command, " the signature of the announcement No. 1, "from 10:00 on January 23,2020, the city's bus, subway, ferry and long-distance passenger services will be suspended. People should not leave Wuhan without special reasons, and the airport and railway stations will be temporarily closed. "

Wuhan Health Commission reported that the current city fever patients increased significantly, there is indeed a fever out-patient long lines, observation bed tension. At the same time, temporary shortage of epidemic prevention materials occurred in different areas of Hubei Province, and medical staff only had simple protection in other areas. Beiqingshen reporters once learned that, as the epidemic continues, provincial health committees have started to increase the allocation of equipment and facilities to designated medical institutions, including gloves, masks and other basic materials.

Liang Yan photographed the medical staff of the fever clinic

Patients with a history of contact with the affected area should be examined

After five days of persistent coughing and a fever of over 38 degrees, viral pneumonia was finally given fluids at around 8:30 pm on January 22.

During the period, Liang Yan in the Shanghai Lung Hospital and Yan Ji Hospital repeatedly to see a doctor. On January 18, Liang Yan's body temperature reached over 38 degrees. She did not see the fever clinic. A nurse at the guide desk of Yan Chai Hospital pointed her to the Emergency Department of Internal Medicine. Since then, because of emergency medical patients too many, Liang Yan and transferred to the emergency department of facial features, were in accordance with the viral cold oral treatment.

On the morning of the 21st, Liang Yan was referred to the lung hospital because his fever remained high and his cough worsened. Liang Yan said that after taking chest x-ray, the doctor felt that there was a problem and asked for a further CT scan. After paying the fee, Liang Yan said, doctors and "throat inflammation may be, we can only treat the lung" for the request for Liang Yan Refund, and transferred back to Yan Chai Hospital.

After being transferred back to Yan Chai Hospital, Liang Yan was transferred to emergency department of facial features, fever outpatient department, aspiration department, Emergency Department of Internal Medicine and other departments. On the afternoon of the 21st, after the emergency department of facial features, Liang Yan finally hung up the fever clinic.

That day, the waiting room of fever clinic was crowded with 40 or 50 patients. It was raining in Shanghai and the patients were squatting in the rain. After nine hours of waiting, Liang was finally seen at 8:30 pm. Meanwhile, due to the long wait time, she also tried to go to the fever clinic of other hospitals, the dense crowd and the long wait were similar, she finally returned to Yan Chai Hospital. Doctors at Yan Chai Hospital's fever clinic ordered a CT scan, and a day after Liang was diagnosed with viral pneumonia, she was finally given fluids in the emergency department.

Although not contact with people from Wuhan, nor to Wuhan, but the current epidemic, the characteristics of human-to-human transmission of the virus so that she was disturbed. She asked Yan Chai Hospital if a sample of her virus could be sent for testing and was subsequently refused. Doctors introduced her to the current hospital procedures: only people with a history of exposure to the Wuhan epidemic area were sent for tests, and even if all other symptoms matched, they could not be sent.

Following a routine pneumonia course, Liang Yan was not quarantined and will receive 10 days of intravenous treatment in the emergency department.

The staff of the Shanghai Pudong District CDC told the reporter that they do not test for virus samples. Only when the hospitals in the district send samples, will they start emergency measures and send samples to the Shanghai CDC for testing, the city only tests samples when it thinks it's necessary. As to what kind of patient specimens can be sent to the test, the staff said, "to judge the hospital, they have done relevant training, trust the hospital. "

In an interview on the 22nd, Liang Yan said doctors told her that they would not send samples of her virus until she became sicker in 10 days and a half months. Until now, Liang did not know what pathogen was causing his pneumonia.

On January 22,23 days after the outbreak, the National Health and Family Planning Commission released a revised version of the COVID-19 pneumonia diagnosis and treatment plan (third edition) , adding the phrase "there are no confirmed cases of Wuhan Travel History. ".

The attending doctor is anxious for protective clothing

At Liang Yan clinic's fever clinic, doctors also have full protective clothing and goggles to wear. But some of the more basic hospital fever clinic, protective clothing just issued, or only simple overalls and masks.

Wang Qiang, who works at a county level second class hospital in the Dongxiang district of Fuzhou, Jiangxi, Jiangxi Province, has yet to see a flood of people returning from Wuhan before protective clothing is handed out to fever clinics.

Wang Qiang was on a shift at the fever clinic when he saw two fever patients from Wuhan on the evening of the 21st. Although the final test result was non viral infection, the number of confirmed and fatal cases was climbing in the news bulletin, still makes the shift doctor nervous without his Hazmat suit.

At the fever clinic, there are now six or seven doctors in charge of treating patients, Wang Qiang told a reporter at one time. It has been more than 20 days since the outbreak in Wuhan, and they are only wearing masks and medical caps.

His fever clinic had never been equipped with protective clothing until a suspected case emerged in a nearby county a few days ago. In recent days, the hospital has conducted a number of internal training, the city organized an emergency video teleconference to the medical staff to introduce the latest diagnostic and treatment guidelines, prevention and control methods and the interpretation of the virus.

However, over the past few days, not only people returning home from Wuhan, but also many patients with fever who have not been to Wuhan have flocked to the clinic. The number of people coming to the fever clinic every day has increased from more than a dozen in the past to dozens, the Hazmat suits haven't been approved by the hospital yet.

The isolation conditions at county hospitals were, in Wang Qiang's view, "rudimentary. ". Although there is a dedicated heating channel for patients with fever, control is not too strict, some patients do not listen to doctors, will act outside the heating channel.

On the afternoon of the 22nd, after another emergency teleconference in the city, Wang Qiang's fever clinic finally got enough protective clothing.

It is reported that Hubei has also appeared in various degrees of epidemic prevention materials shortage phenomenon. According to the calculation of the relevant departments, as of the 31st of this month, Hubei Province can only produce 8 million medical masks, 2 million protective clothing, 1,200 infrared thermometers, can not meet the epidemic prevention needs of the province. Therefore, Hubei Province plans to request the urgent support to the country, allocates the medical mask 40 million, the protective clothing 5 million, the infrared thermometer 5000 sets.

On the evening of the 22nd, the deputy mayor of Wuhan, Chen Xiangxin, said that currently Wuhan has adopted a "7 + 7" medical prevention and treatment method, namely from seven large general hospitals in Wuhan, including Tongji, Xiehe, Provincial People's Hospital and Zhongnan Hospital, in twinning with seven municipal hospitals, it plans to free up 3,400 beds for patients with fevers. The figure, announced the day before by the city's health and health commission, was 2,000 beds for pneumonia patients. The two-day figure adds up to at least 5,400 beds in Wuhan.

In-house emergency training at Taikang County People's Hospital

Grass-roots hospitals to step up emergency training

On January 21, Zhejiang Province confirmed the first case of COVID-19 pneumonia. The diagnosis was confirmed three times: On the 17th, the provincial CDC tested positive for COVID-19; on the 20th, the specimen was sent to the CDC for reexamination, and the result was positive; on the 21st, the case was confirmed by the expert assessment of the diagnostic team set up under the epidemic leading group of the National Health Commission.

A notice was posted on the side of the guiding desk of a county people's Hospital in Zhejiang Province: For the health of your family, please tell me whether you have been to Wuhan.

Three days ago, the hospital had a pneumonia patient from Wuhan, after the hospital transferred the patient to the fever clinic for observation. According to the director of the hospital, after taking blood samples from patients, the hospital transported the samples by ambulance and sent them directly to the laboratory of the Municipal Center for Disease Control for testing. The results were received about six hours later, and the patient's nucleic acid test was negative, to Rule Out COVID-19 infection.

The hospital president told the deep once reporters, the current provincial requirements, if there are suspected patients can not be arbitrarily transferred to hospital, need to ask for instructions from the higher authorities, by the higher experts sent to assess the decision. If the patient is transferred after diagnosis, it is necessary to use the negative pressure cart transport, transfer personnel should wear protective clothing, and through the designated route to the designated location. The director also said patients with fever from Wuhan were banned from seeing doctors in community hospitals and needed to go to designated fever clinics for centralized treatment.

The first confirmed case of COVID-19 pneumonia in Henan Province was treated by inhalation in the People's Hospital of Taikang County, Zhoukou City, Henan Province, on January 8, and was hospitalized for two days under isolation. On the evening of January 22, a reporter visited the Taikang County People's Hospital and found that most of the hospital staff were wearing surgical masks, while most of the patients who came to the hospital did not wear masks, many in-patients and family members also do not wear masks.

A number of hospital security personnel told the reporter, they are January 22 morning only received the hospital issued masks, uniform wear.

On the afternoon of January 22, an internal emergency training session on how to prevent and diagnose COVID-19 pneumonia was held at a designated county-level pneumonia hospital in Xinyang, Henan Province.

According to Kang Jian, director of the Emergency Department of the hospital, as far as diagnosis is concerned, the first thing for a patient to ask is an epidemiological history, whether he or she has been to an infected area, or has come into contact with someone who has returned from an infected area. The second thing is to look at the clinical symptoms, if fever, dry cough, and other symptoms, also need to do a blood test, if the white blood cells are not high or low, lymphocyte, consider whether the virus infection. In addition, a nucleic acid test is required for chest x-ray examination if interstitial pneumonia is present. "At present, the county does not have the conditions for nucleic acid testing, " Kang said. "The hospital collects the patient's throat test paper, sputum and serum, and then sends them to the Municipal Center for Disease Control and Prevention for testing. The final diagnosis depends on experts from the province. "

That's pretty much how all the designated hospitals handle it. At the triage point, nurses put masks on patients, take their temperature and ask about their epidemiological history, such as whether they traveled, worked or lived in Wuhan before the onset of symptoms, said Liu Yansong, deputy director of the Huazhong University of Science and Technology and Shenzhen Hospital, whether has been exposed to Wuhan new type pneumonia patient, whether the contact wildlife and so on. Patients who meet the relevant criteria will be triaged to the fever clinic.

Regarding the protection of medical personnel, Kang said that the current protection is divided into three levels, "The first level of protection is normal wear work clothes and medical masks. The second level is in fever clinics and infection areas. If there are suspected cases, wear isolation clothes. The third level of protection requires wearing protective glasses and other equipment. "

According to Kang, although the medical conditions and diagnostic level are much better than during the SARS period and no suspected cases have yet been found in the hospital, "but I am very worried because we are too close to Wuhan. "

At present, all cases need to be confirmed by provincial level CDC

Sun Xiaodong, deputy director of the Shanghai Center for Disease Control and Prevention, said in an interview with the media earlier that all current cases need to be tested and confirmed by the laboratory of the provincial center for Disease Control and Prevention, district Centers for Disease Control and medical institutions do not assume the task of virus detection. At present, the confirmed cases will be treated in isolation. For close contacts, the current measures of isolation have concentrated isolation or home isolation, isolation days are generally 14 days.

Sun Xiaodong said frankly that for patients with pneumonia of unknown cause, the time needed to go through from discovery to diagnosis varies, not only because testing takes time, but also because it requires an epidemiological survey of the patients, master the track of their previous activities, work and rest patterns.

"For example, where this person has been, what he has eaten, what people and animals he has come into contact with, Wuhan has previously established that many cases of pneumonia of unknown origin are linked to the south China Seafood Market, and that these are the results of detailed epidemiological investigations, " Sun said, for similar new infectious disease, as with "solving a case, " each case and its family need to actively assist the health authorities in conducting investigations and keeping them informed of recent movements, etc. , this will help to control the spread of the epidemic.

Issued and implemented by the State Council on May 9,2003, and amended in 2011, the regulations on emergency response to Public Health Emergencies (hereinafter referred to as "the regulations") set strict limits on the reporting procedures and time limits for epidemic situations, the State Council shall be aware of the epidemic within nine hours at the latest in response to major and emergency epidemics.

At the same time, "regulations" for major outbreaks can be reported over the level. The county health bureau, while reporting to the county government, must simultaneously report to the Municipal Bureau of Health and the Ministry of Health; the county government, while reporting to the municipal government, may also report to the provincial government; and the state will publish the emergency reporting telephone number, all units and individuals have the right to report potential emergencies to the Government of the People's Republic of China and its relevant departments.

Hong Kong, Macau and other countries with confirmed cases of COVID-19 pneumonia have also stepped up surveillance and quarantine measures. As of 21 January 2020, a total of 118 suspected cases have been reported in Hong Kong, of which 88 have been discharged and no confirmed cases have been reported. The Secretary for Food and Health of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region government said at a press conference that, the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region government has strengthened the screening of suspected cases, implemented a health declaration system for flights from Wuhan to Hong Kong, and conducted temperature checks on Wuhan visitors to Hong Kong. Public hospitals continue to implement disease visiting measures, there are enough protective equipment for three months and 500 negative pressure isolation beds.
